on actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n\n\n{{India-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Irshad Ali\n| image       =\n| birth_date  = \n| birth_name  =  Irshad Ali\n| birth_place = [[Thrissur]], [[Kerala]], India\n| nationality  = Indian\n| parents     = Abdu, Nafisa<ref name=\"mathrubhumi1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/malayalam/400653/ |accessdate=24 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131024035513/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/malayalam/400653/ |archivedate=24 October 2013 }}</ref>\n| spouse      =  Ramseena\n| children     =  Arshaq\n}}\n\n'''Irshad''' (also known Irshad ali)  is an Indian actor in [[Malayalam]] films. He hails from [[Kechery]], [[Thrissur]] .<ref>[http://www.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/malayalamContentView.do?contentId=14801315&programId=1073752204&channelId=-1073750705&BV_ID=@@@&tabId=3] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203010126/http://www.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/malayalamContentView.do?contentId=14801315&programId=1073752204&channelId=-1073750705&BV_ID=@@@&tabId=3 |date=3 December 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nIrshad has acted in numerous award-winning [[Art film|art-house films]] including those directed by acclaimed filmmakers such as [[V. K. Pavithran|Pavithran]], [[T. V. Chandran]], [[P. T. Kunju Muhammed]], and [[K. R. Mohanan]]. He has also appeared in supporting roles in a few mainstream films. He debuted as an actor in [[Sibi Malayil]]'s campus story ''Pranayavarnangal'' (''Colours of Love'', 1998). ''Garshom'' (1999), his first offbeat film, gave him a place in [[parallel cinema]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/863/ |accessdate=19 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219091055/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies/interview/863/ |archivedate=19 December 2013 }}</ref> Several significant roles in parallel cinema made him a well-known face in art house movies. His notable films include T. V. Chandran's ''[[Dany (film)|Dany]]'' (2002), ''[[Paadam Onnu: Oru Vilapam]]'' (''Lesson One: A Wail'', 2003), ''[[Vilapangalkkappuram]]'' (2008) and ''[[Bhoomi Malayalam]]'' (''The Mother Earth'', 2009), P. T. Kunju Muhammed's ''[[Paradesi (2007 film)|Paradesi]]'' (''Foreigner'', 2007), [[Madhu Kaithapram]]'s ''[[Madhya Venal]]'' (2009), [[Priyanandanan]]'s ''[[Pulijanmam]]'' (''Tiger Life'', 2006) and ''[[Bhakthajanangalude Sradhakku]]'' (2011), and Dr. Biju's ''[[Veettilekkulla Vazhi]]'' (''The Way Home'', 2010).<ref>Rasmi Binoy. (5 May 2011). [http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1993529.ece \"Career moves\"]. ''The Hindu''. Retrieved 9 May 2011.</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is born to Puthenpura Nalakathu Abdu and Nafeesa, as fourth son among six children, at [[Kechery]], [[Thrissur]]. He has four brothers and a sister.<ref>[http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/254669?page=0,0 \u0d06\u0d23\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2a\u0d46\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d23\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d1a\u0d41\u0d02\u0d2c\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d3e\u0d32\u0d4d\u200d \u0d32\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d02 \u0d07\u0d1f\u0d3f\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e\u0d41\u0d35\u0d40\u0d34\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d4b? | mangalam.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He is married to Ramseena, a bank employee. They have a son, Arshaq.<ref name=\"mathrubhumi1\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !!Director\n\n\n|-\n|2020\n|[[Draft:Operation Java|''Operation Java'']]\n|\n|Tharun Moorthy\n|-\n|2020\n|''Silencer''\n|\n|[[Priyanandanan|Priyanandan]]\n|-\n|2019||''[[My Santa (2019 filim)]]''|| ||[[Sugeeth]]\n|-\n|2019||''Vikruthi''|| ||\n|-\n-\n|2019|| ''[[Thanneer Mathan Dinangal]]''||Principal || Gireesh A D\n|-\n|2019|| ''[[Sayanna Varthakal]]''||{{TBA}} || Arun Chandu\n|-\n|2018|| ''[[Joseph]]''|| Siddique || [[M. 